article.headline: North Carolina A&T 70, HOWARD 66
article.story: GREENSBORO, N.C. (AP) -- Jason Wills scored 17 points and pulled down 10 rebounds to lead North Carolina A&T over Howard 70-66 on Monday night. Greg Roberts and Austin Erwing added 16 point apiece for the Aggies (6-9, 2-1 Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference), who led 36-30 at the break. Roberts also had nine rebounds, and Steven Rush added 10 points. Darryl Hudson had 18 points and nine rebounds for Howard (6-10, 2-2 MEAC), while Will Gant added 15 points and Darek Mitchell finished with 14. Gant led Howard in 3-pointers, going 5-for-10 from outside the arc. Howard made 11 of its 30 attempted 3-pointers, while North Carolina A&T netted only four of its 17 attempted 3-pointers.
